    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The swelling of clay objects during firing as gases are released in the vitrification process; sometimes caused by overfiring and occurs either generally or in small areas; generally considered a defect in pottery but sometimes desirable in nonbearing bricks for construction.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
